:INFO
The Second Read at a Different Age
I first read The Kite Runner at 22 and it moved me the way books move you when \
you are young: completely and without complication. I reread it at 37. The \
experience was different in almost every way. Not because the book had changed \
but because I had. The sections about fathers and sons, about guilt carried over \
decades, about what it costs to be a bystander rather than someone who acts, \
all of these landed in places the younger version of me did not yet have.

